remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` is the recommended way to construct complex paths programmatically.
Add contours using methods such as `MoveTo`, `LineTo`, `CubicTo`, and `Close`,
then call `Snapshot` to obtain a read-only `SKPath` without resetting the builder,
or `Detach` to transfer ownership of the path and reset the builder.

This type wraps a native Skia resource and implements `IDisposable`. Always
dispose of it when done, either with a `using` statement or by calling
`Dispose()` directly.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(10, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.Close();

using var path = builder.Snapshot();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
